//github.com/open-telemetry/semantic-conventions-java/tree/v1.30.0/semconv/src/test\" in /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge9/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5784-eff6f629\nexec\n/usr/bin/bash -lc \"curl -I -L -s -o /dev/null -w '%{http_code} %{url_effective}\\\\n' https://github.com/open-telemetry/semantic-conventions-java\" in /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge9/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5784-eff6f629\n succeeded in 572ms:\n200 https://github.com/open-telemetry/semantic-conventions-java/tree/v1.30.0/semconv/src/test\n\n succeeded in 666ms:\n200 https://github.com/open-telemetry/semantic-conventions-java\n\nweb search: \nweb search: https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/io/opentelemetry/semconv/opentelemetry-semconv/1.30.0/\nweb search: \nweb search: 'Java generated classes for semantic conventions' in https://github.com/open-telemetry/semantic-conventions-java\ncodex\nI’ve verified the rendered source, javadoc, repository, and test URLs all return HTTP 200 for `1.30.0`. I’m going to add those missing fields to only the `metadata-version: 1.30.0` entry and leave `language` absent because this is a Java artifact, not one of the Kotlin/Groovy/Scala language-specific cases.\napply patch\npatch: completed\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge9/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5784-eff6f629/metadata/io.opentelemetry.semconv/opentelemetry-semconv/index.json\ndiff --git a/metadata/io.opentelemetry.semconv/opentelemetry-semconv/index.json b/metadata/io.opentelemetry.semconv/opentelemetry-semconv/index.json\nindex 6f3f3d8cb00059cf07d33d4e0e717e7a9dd9c03d..b7da1c20cfdef6e413b5a7e8281b76840c2b84a7\n--- a/metadata/io.opentelemetry.semconv/opentelemetry-semconv/index.json\n+++ b/metadata/io.opentelemetry.semconv/opentelemetry-semconv/index.json\n@@ -34,6 +34,11 @@\n   },\n   {\n     \"metadata-version\" : \"1.30.0\",\n+    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/io/opent