c attributes defined by the OpenTelemetry specification. Applications and instrumentation libraries use it to refer to telemetry attributes consistently when producing traces, metrics, logs, and resource metadata.\",\n     \"tested-versions\" : [\n       \"1.30.0\"\n     ],\n\ncodex\nThe edit is in place. I’m validating the JSON and the repository’s metadata checks for that coordinate so we catch formatting or schema issues before handing it back.\nexec\n/usr/bin/bash -lc \"jq '.[] | select(.\\\"metadata-version\\\" == \\\"1.30.0\\\")' metadata/io.opentelemetry.semconv/opentelemetry-semconv/index.json\" in /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge9/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5784-eff6f629\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
